Protocol Implementations

Hypercolor implements device communication protocols derived from publicly available
sources. All driver implementations are clean-room Rust code based on published protocol
specifications, community documentation, and packet captures. No proprietary software
was decompiled or disassembled.

Sources referenced for protocol knowledge:

- OpenRGB project — protocol documentation and community research (GPL-2.0)
  https://gitlab.com/CalcProgrammer1/OpenRGB
- openrazer — community reverse-engineering wiki and documentation
  https://github.com/openrazer/openrazer
- uchroma — Rust HID report builder and Python protocol abstractions
  https://github.com/hyperb1iss/uchroma
- liquidctl — AIO and fan controller protocol documentation
  https://github.com/liquidctl/liquidctl
- uni-sync — PrismRGB protocol implementation in Rust
  https://github.com/EightB1ts/uni-sync
- WLED project — UDP/HTTP protocol documentation
  https://kno.wled.ge/
- ASUS community — Aura/ENE protocol reverse-engineering documentation
- QMK firmware — HID RGB vendor protocol specification
  https://qmk.fm/

Vendored Dependencies

- midir (vendor/midir/) — MIDI I/O library, patched for Hypercolor's use case
  Original: https://github.com/Boddlnagg/midir
  License: MIT
